1. create a project in eclipse, name it as BankingProject

2. create packages
	1. accounts
	2. transactions
	
3. In account package create a class by name account identify attributes, apply java bean class structure

4. create a class in account package
	purpose: responsible to create an account object return it
	className: AccountCreation
	method:
		methodName: createAccount
		parameter: same as attribute of account
		return type: Account type
		
5. create a class in transaction 
	purpose: class is responsible to do withdrawal transaction
	className: WithdrawTransaction
	method:
		methodName: withdraw
		parameter: two parameters
				1. Account type
				2. double type
		return type: boolean
		
6. create a class in transaction 
purpose: class is responsible to do deposit transaction
className: DepositTransaction
method:
	methodName: deposit
	parameter: two parameters
			1. Account type
			2. double type
	return type: void
	
7. create a class in transaction 
purpose: class is responsible to do fund transfer transaction
className: FundTransfer
method:
	methodName: transfer
	parameter: two parameters
			1. Account type
			2. Account type
			3. double type
	return type: boolean
	
8. create a class in transaction 
purpose: class is responsible to print account balance
className: ViewAccountBalance
method:
	methodName: viewBalance
	parameter: one parameters
			1. Account type
	return type: void
	
	
Main method flow:
	Create new package app
	inside write MainClass

1. Create 2 account by using AccountCreation
2. Create all transaction class objects
3. Check Balance of first account
4. Deposit x amount to first account
5. Withdraw x amount from first account
6. Transfer x amount from first account to second account
7. Check Balance of both accounts